        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "07a27fb5-499e-407d-b938-558dc776b877",
        "text": "In 1969, a law (the ''Berufsbildungsgesetz'') was passed which regulated and unified the vocational training system and codified the shared responsibility of the state, the unions, associations and the chambers of trade and industry. The dual system was successful in both parts of the divided Germany. In the GDR ([[German Democratic Republic]]), three-quarters of the working population had completed apprenticeships."
